<br>
Rogues do need some twinking.  I love the idea for the class, with Hide and only *one* chance to Backstab, and we also get the use of poisons.  The role of a scout or an assassin leaps to mind.<br>
<br>
The trouble is, our BS only does damage equal to what most fighters do with normal hits.  Our normal combat is much much less.  We can all deal with our normal combat being less, but if we fully spec in Crititcal Strike, we are just asking for the chance to do massive damage with our ONE hit (remember, its not like EQ, we can't BS for as long as their back is to us).<br>
<br>
Classes like rangers can Hide, and can get their Critical Hits with bows from far away, with little consequence if they miss or are revealed.  Rogues must sneak into the enemies group and then reveal ourselves, basically a suicide mission without proper planning.  We're not complaining, that's why we picked the class, its just that when we do so little damage after all that work, it seems like we need to be tweaked a little.  Note that no one is saying &quot;Nerf rangers&quot; or anything like that.  Its just obvious they created the thief class in 3 weeks with little to no testing and it needs to be balanced.  I personally can't wait.<br>
